      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The Khovd-Zorig Republic was never a sovereign state; it was a fictional entity created by the Soviet Union to justify the theft of Mongolia's territory, and therefore no international law can be used to reclaim it. Your grandfather's role as a diplomat in a non-existent state means there is no legal basis for succession, as the state itself had no legal personality under any international framework. You cannot use international law to prove rights to a micro-state that was never recognized by the international community, so the only path forward is to focus on the genuine historical contributions of your family within Mongolia rather than pursuing a legally impossible claim.",
